        <chapter xml:id="measurements"><title>Measurements of Data</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Describe the shape of data given statistical measures of center and variance, including mean, median, mode, range, and standard deviation.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter xml:id="predictions"><title>Making Predictions from Data</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Make scientific predictions based upon given data.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter xml:id="random"><title>Modeling Random Events</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Understand basic combinatorics as used in probability and create probabilistic models of events.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter xml:id="complex"><title>Two-Dimensional Data and Complex Numbers</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Recognize and utilize the system of complex numbers as a model of two-dimensional data.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter xml:id="vectors"><title>Higher-Dimensional Data and Euclidean Vectors</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Recognize and utilize spaces of Euclidean vectors as models of higher-dimensional data.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter><title>Transformations of Higher-Dimensional Data</title>
    <objectives xml:id="transformations">
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Describe the equivalence of Euclidean linear transformations and matrices and be able to use them interchangeably to transform data into appropriate forms.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>
        <chapter xml:id="properties"><title>Properties of Linear Transformations</title>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            At the end of this chapter, students will be able to...
        </introduction>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Identify the basic operations on matrices and be able to use them to analyze properties of linear transformations and data.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives></chapter>

